SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13
14
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-35 of Title 2, unless there is
14
15
created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15
16
A. There is hereby created within the Oklahoma Department of
16
17
Agriculture, Food, and Forestry, the Advisory Council on Product
17
18
Classification.
18
19
B. The Council shall serve solely in an advisory role and shall
19
20
advise and make recommendations to the Department regarding the
20
21
classification of agriculture and food products for purposes
21
22
conducted by the Department.
22
23
C. The Council shall be composed of five (5) members appointed
23
24
by the State Board of Agriculture, all of whom shall represent
24
